&lt;p&gt;We&#39;re looking for a Head of Quality Engineering to join our technology function, reporting directly to the CTO. At Xapo, we are building truly cross-functional teams with full ownership of design, architecture, building, testing, delivery, data, and operations, structured as Stream Aligned Teams (SATs), Platform teams and Enabling teams as per Team Topologies.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This role owns the quality framework across the entire technology function, coverage standards, gate criteria, AI-assisted test tooling, SAT enablement, and pre-release veto authority. You give engineering, apps, and web a single accountable owner for what &quot;quality&quot; means and how it is measured.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is not a traditional QA role. You will not sit in a test team checking other people&#39;s code, SAT engineers own quality in their own code (shift-left). You own the system engineers test within: the framework, the tooling, the gates, and the standards.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The role is deliberately tooling-heavy over headcount-heavy. Your budget is for tooling and AI tokens, not for building a QA team beneath you. The agentic QA pipeline is already in active PoC with positive early results; you will own scaling it to production. Your north star: fully automated quality enforcement, where releases are blocked automatically when rigorous checks fail, without needing human intervention. Target: more than 80% of release quality decisions made by automated tooling within 12 months of hire.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is an opportunity to shape how a regulated crypto bank defines and enforces software quality,&amp;nbsp; at the intersection of engineering excellence, AI-assisted tooling, and a genuinely high-stakes production environment.&lt;/p&gt;
