&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Quality framework definition: own coverage standards (unit, service, integration, end-to-end), gate criteria, and the quality contribution to the function-level Definition of Done. Aligned with Head of Engineering on backend and Head of Frontend Engineering on client-side.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Coverage baselines: define measurable coverage thresholds per service and per tribe, with trend visibility, and drive adoption across teams.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Pre-release veto authority: hold and exercise the authority to block releases when quality gates are not met. Own the automated tooling that makes this veto self-triggering rather than dependent on a single person.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;AI-assisted test tooling: define and drive the framework for automated test generation, regression coverage, integration test tooling, and the agentic QA pipeline. You are the designer and driver; implementation is a cross-functional effort with Platform, backend, web, and mobile engineers.&lt;/li&gt;
